label.value: regulation of dendrite extension

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite extension.

definition.value: An example of this is Mul1 in mouse (UniProt ID Q8VCM5) in PMID:24898855 inferred from mutant phenotype.

label.value: negative regulation of dendrite extension

value.value: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite extension.

definition.value: An example of this is Mul1 in mouse (UniProt ID Q8VCM5) in PMID:24898855 inferred from mutant phenotype.

value.value: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of dendrite extension.

definition.value: An example of this is Mul1 in mouse (UniProt ID Q8VCM5) in PMID:24898855 inferred from mutant phenotype.
